001package com.commercetools.graphql.api.client;
002
003import com.commercetools.graphql.api.types.CategoryDraft;
004import com.netflix.graphql.dgs.client.codegen.GraphQLQuery;
005import java.lang.Override;
006import java.lang.String;
007import java.util.HashSet;
008import java.util.Set;
009
010public class CreateCategoryGraphQLQuery extends GraphQLQuery {
011  public CreateCategoryGraphQLQuery(CategoryDraft draft, String queryName, Set<String> fieldsSet) {
012    super("mutation", queryName);
013    if (draft != null || fieldsSet.contains("draft")) {
014        getInput().put("draft", draft);
015    }
016  }
017
018  public CreateCategoryGraphQLQuery() {
019    super("mutation");
020  }
021
022  @Override
023  public String getOperationName() {
024     return "createCategory";
025                    
026  }
027
028  public static Builder newRequest() {
029    return new Builder();
030  }
031
032  public static class Builder {
033    private Set<String> fieldsSet = new HashSet<>();
034
035    private CategoryDraft draft;
036
037    private String queryName;
038
039    public CreateCategoryGraphQLQuery build() {
040      return new CreateCategoryGraphQLQuery(draft, queryName, fieldsSet);
041               
042    }
043
044    public Builder draft(CategoryDraft draft) {
045      this.draft = draft;
046      this.fieldsSet.add("draft");
047      return this;
048    }
049
050    public Builder queryName(String queryName) {
051      this.queryName = queryName;
052      return this;
053    }
054  }
055}
